WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.737
Well, good evening family.

00:00:01.737 --> 00:00:06.490
Thank you for joining us again tonight, and good morning to all of you in Australia.

00:00:06.490 --> 00:00:12.880
I don't know what time it is over there, but I like to say good morning all the time, even when it is not morning.

00:00:13.720 --> 00:00:16.097
We have a lot to talk about tonight.

00:00:16.931 --> 00:00:24.364
We have these clips Braden made for us, and he'll be adding new things to the back of the screen.

00:00:24.364 --> 00:00:25.740
He works so hard at it.

00:00:25.740 --> 00:00:28.640
I told him, 'Let's do two nights in a row of that.

00:00:28.640 --> 00:00:36.613
' He worked so hard on the prophetic mural.

00:00:37.633 --> 00:00:41.360
It's needed, even though my head's covering all of it.

00:00:41.360 --> 00:00:43.200
Well, you weren't here last night, that's why.

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:45.373
But I'd rather have you here than that.

00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:49.950
Come get closer to me.

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:54.650
Let's go over some of the things in the news.

00:00:55.200 --> 00:01:05.840
I want to start right off by saying this: I thought it was amazing last night because I went over everything the Lord showed us at the end of the broadcast—when it happened, how it happened, and everything.

00:01:15.634 --> 00:01:18.153
Excuse me, that's why I'm sitting.

00:01:18.153 --> 00:01:20.320
I just had greasy food.

00:01:21.070 --> 00:01:27.070
I took a bite of that bread.

00:01:27.080 --> 00:01:33.977
It wasn't until I said, 'Don't you see?

00:01:33.977 --> 00:01:35.440
I can't do anything.

00:01:35.440 --> 00:01:37.914
I don't have control of it,' and it was a flatline.

00:01:37.914 --> 00:01:41.640
It was like touching a cold stove last night.

00:01:41.640 --> 00:01:53.933
But the moment I gave Jesus the praise, the moment I acknowledged him, it switched on and I started seeing.

00:01:54.720 --> 00:02:06.280
He said, 'If you give me praise and glory and touch not the glory, touch not the anointing, every time you do this, I'll show up like that.

00:02:06.280 --> 00:02:08.587
' But last night I didn't, because I don't want to be redundant.

00:02:08.587 --> 00:02:11.380
It's like repeating things over and over again.

00:02:11.380 --> 00:02:14.720
Brandon can't do anything apart from him.

00:02:14.720 --> 00:02:21.120
Anything I see, anything that's shown to us by the spirit of God, is all because of God.

00:02:21.302 --> 00:02:23.960
I say it every single time and I'll continue to say it.

00:02:23.960 --> 00:02:26.960
Last night was a perfect example.

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:30.880
I avoided trying to go over it, and there it was—it was a flatline.

00:02:30.880 --> 00:02:38.090
I did the whole broadcast and showed you all the things until I said, 'Well, excuse me, here we are folks.

00:02:38.090 --> 00:02:56.640
' I thought it was amazing because the moment I gave him acknowledgement, the moment I said it out of my mouth—apart from him, I can do nothing; we give all the glory to Jesus—I started seeing instantaneously.

00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:58.480
It was amazing.

00:02:59.047 --> 00:03:00.846
The broadcast went on for three hours.

00:03:02.876 --> 00:03:07.560
I said I couldn't get in the river no matter how hard I tried.

00:03:07.885 --> 00:03:15.115
Even today, whenever he took me and I was in my prayer time, he said, 'Brandon'—I said, 'What is going on?

00:03:15.115 --> 00:03:16.000
How are things going today?

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:17.667
' just talking like I always do to him.

00:03:17.667 --> 00:03:22.550
And he said, 'Brandon, I want you to start enjoying life more.

00:03:22.560 --> 00:03:25.640
You're taking too much of this on you.

00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:29.480
I want you to have fun and enjoy life.

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:34.150
' I said, 'I get it.

00:03:34.160 --> 00:03:38.160
' He said, 'Tell my people to have more fun.

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:41.600
Tell my people to enjoy life more.

00:03:41.600 --> 00:03:44.960
Life's supposed to be fun and good.

00:03:44.960 --> 00:03:48.920
I gave you life, and life more abundantly.

00:03:48.920 --> 00:04:01.280
' So many people are like me—the pressure of life, the pressure of the prophetic, the pressure of all of it tries to choke the fun out of things.

00:04:01.436 --> 00:04:03.640
He said, 'I want you just to have fun.

00:04:03.640 --> 00:04:05.560
Laugh more.

00:04:06.640 --> 00:04:08.800
Enjoy your family more.

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:14.880
You don't have to walk under the pressure of things.

00:04:14.880 --> 00:04:17.160
It's not yours to carry.

00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:19.560
' Yesterday was a prime example of it.

00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:26.650
I remember Rodney Howard-Browne telling a story—and I don't talk about names, but I remember this story.

00:04:26.650 --> 00:04:39.490
He brought it up to me where he was over at some pastor's house before the service and he was playing video games with the pastor's son.

00:04:41.800 --> 00:04:52.400
The pastor got so upset that he was not praying before the service; he was not taking it more seriously in his mind.

00:04:52.400 --> 00:05:02.423
But Rodney felt to play the game with the son, and the glory fell in that service.

00:05:08.544 --> 00:05:08.880
The bottom line is, it is in us.

00:05:08.880 --> 00:05:23.107
Regardless of whether you're having fun and enjoying life, or you're relaxing and resting, there's a point where you think it's self-righteousness that brings the glory.

00:05:23.107 --> 00:05:31.840
'Well, it's because I fasted five times this week,' and 'It's because I put myself in position.

00:05:31.840 --> 00:05:49.575
' Not saying that doesn't help your flesh to be crucified, but if you have the mindset that it's because of what I did that got me qualified to get this, you already disqualified yourself.

00:05:49.575 --> 00:05:52.540
The Lord was showing me it's about relationship.

00:05:52.540 --> 00:05:54.973
He said, 'Brandon, it's about relationship.

00:05:54.973 --> 00:06:17.080
' Do you realize it's not about how much you think—'I didn't say anything rude today to Diana; I tried really hard to always walk in love'—when you're in a marriage and you work with somebody seven days a week, 24 hours a day, you have a tendency to be cranky and crunchy.

00:06:17.080 --> 00:06:22.265
I tell her, 'It's not about even that.

00:06:22.265 --> 00:06:26.806
' 'Well, I disqualified myself today; I had a bad attitude.

00:06:26.806 --> 00:06:34.594
' You always want to walk in love, but that's not the point.

00:06:34.594 --> 00:06:44.497
I'm trying to say that it's not how good you think you are that qualifies you for the glory.

00:06:44.497 --> 00:06:48.780
You're human, and you always lean on him.

00:06:50.107 --> 00:06:57.102
You are always leaning on and trusting in him regardless of how messed up you are.

00:07:08.850 --> 00:07:08.995
It's all about Jesus.

00:07:16.125 --> 00:07:16.510
It's just a mindset of relationship that he's been teaching me about.

00:07:16.510 --> 00:07:19.660
It's always something like, 'Well, I prayed extra long today.

00:07:19.660 --> 00:07:25.560
' We drove a lot more today and looked for stuff for our eBay store.

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:27.467
'You prayed a lot longer today, Brandon.

00:07:27.467 --> 00:07:35.760
Boy, I bet tonight's broadcast is going to be over the top because you prayed in tongues for six hours.

00:07:37.580 --> 00:07:38.200
I bet you're qualified tonight, buddy.

00:07:38.200 --> 00:07:46.840
' That's why the Lord told me, 'Brandon, even on your worst day, it's my grace.

00:07:46.840 --> 00:08:05.495
No matter how much you have it in your mind to think that you're qualified tonight to see and be able to do anything in the spirit realm with me, you never were good enough in the first place.

00:08:05.495 --> 00:08:07.980
It was always by my grace and by the blood.

00:08:07.980 --> 00:08:14.531
' It goes back to when I stepped on the dog and killed it.

00:08:14.531 --> 00:08:20.480
If anyone hasn't heard that before, my little girl got a dog for Christmas.

00:08:20.480 --> 00:08:24.480
Diana, I'm glad you're here; you can chime in.

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:27.187
Don't sit over there and be quiet.

00:08:33.816 --> 00:08:34.033
I was playing Warzone, Call of Duty, with Braden for Christmas.

00:08:40.165 --> 00:08:40.440
I'm really competitive and we like to win.

00:08:40.440 --> 00:08:42.052
Braden's really good at Call of Duty.

00:08:42.052 --> 00:08:46.302
For all the religious ones out there: Oh my gosh, I can't believe...

00:08:46.302 --> 00:08:47.349
No, no, no.

00:08:47.349 --> 00:08:53.293
I have fun with my son and we play as a team.

00:08:53.293 --> 00:08:58.560
Braden wins; he's very good at Call of Duty.

00:09:08.180 --> 00:09:08.520
I'm not so good.

00:09:12.470 --> 00:09:17.187
I was really focused and wasn't paying attention, but I told Paisley to put the dog up several times.

00:09:17.187 --> 00:09:21.160
It was a brand new puppy and she had it wrapped in a blanket.

00:09:21.580 --> 00:09:26.900
I jumped up to go to the bathroom in between matches.

00:09:26.900 --> 00:09:34.613
I'm a big guy, of course, and I stepped on this puppy and killed it right there.

00:09:36.600 --> 00:09:37.120
Squashed it.

00:09:37.120 --> 00:09:39.227
The guts popped out.

00:09:41.760 --> 00:09:47.670
I mean, this is how I squashed and destroyed this dog right there.

00:09:47.680 --> 00:09:54.566
Instantaneously, Paisley is like, 'You—' because the dog is dead.

00:09:54.748 --> 00:09:55.292
I lost it.

00:09:55.292 --> 00:10:03.464
I'm cussing, acting a fool, because I'm so mad about what I just did.

00:10:19.271 --> 00:10:19.476
I'm blaming myself, but instantaneously you start blaming other people.

00:10:19.476 --> 00:10:20.573
'It's your fault.

00:10:20.573 --> 00:10:22.705
' No, it's my fault.

00:10:23.395 --> 00:10:24.085
I was stupid.

00:10:25.120 --> 00:10:27.940
I should have watched where I was walking.

00:10:27.940 --> 00:10:35.956
But I lost my cool and started saying all kinds of profanity.

00:10:36.151 --> 00:10:45.120
I was freaking out because the dog we just bought for Christmas was dead; it had been squashed.

00:10:45.120 --> 00:10:47.200
This was years ago.

00:10:47.200 --> 00:10:50.670
I just want to clarify that this was a long time ago.

00:10:50.670 --> 00:10:57.200
You don't have to defend me; it is what it is.

00:11:05.430 --> 00:11:05.585
I was a jerk and killed the dog.

00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:06.205
I lost it.

00:11:15.364 --> 00:11:15.587
I went in the back and Paisley started screaming, 'Daddy, aren't you going to pray for my dog to rise from the dead?

00:11:15.587 --> 00:11:18.449
Daddy, don't you believe God will raise my dog from the dead?

00:11:18.449 --> 00:11:22.813
' I said, 'God's not going to hear me at all.

00:11:22.813 --> 00:11:23.200
Honey, I'm not there.

00:11:28.876 --> 00:11:29.112
I lost it.

00:11:41.113 --> 00:11:41.347
I'm just not there.

00:11:41.347 --> 00:11:43.400
' I said, 'But you pray; I can't.

00:11:43.400 --> 00:11:49.280
' She said, 'All things are possible to him who believes, Daddy.

00:11:49.280 --> 00:11:53.992
Pray for my dog to get up from the dead.

00:11:53.992 --> 00:12:00.820
' I told her I couldn't do it and that He wouldn't hear me.

00:12:07.753 --> 00:12:08.847
So she started marching up and down the hallway, screaming as loud as she could, 'All things are possible!

00:12:08.847 --> 00:12:14.824
' praying in the Holy Spirit, 'Get up from the dead, dog!

00:12:14.824 --> 00:12:16.926
Get up from the dead!

00:12:16.926 --> 00:12:20.440
' She was weeping because her dog was dead.

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:30.344
Several hours later, Diana put the dog in a shoebox.

00:12:30.344 --> 00:12:45.280
It was frozen outside with snow on the ground, and I thought, 'I'm not going to go out there and dig a hole in that frozen ground right now.

00:12:45.280 --> 00:12:58.114
' So we put the dog in a shoebox and set it by the trash can on the front porch.

00:13:06.880 --> 00:13:07.280
I told her I'd take care of it later.

00:13:07.280 --> 00:13:20.758
Diana put the dog out there and I felt bad later.

00:13:35.240 --> 00:13:35.495
The Holy Spirit jumped all over me because I had acted like an idiot.

00:13:41.160 --> 00:13:41.520
I was broken.

00:13:41.520 --> 00:13:44.907
I went in and told her I was sorry.

00:13:44.907 --> 00:13:46.540
Paisley was still crying.

00:13:46.540 --> 00:13:56.343
I admitted I was an idiot and apologized for yelling.

00:13:56.343 --> 00:14:10.137
Then Diana went to take the trash out to the porch, and the dog was gone.

00:14:10.137 --> 00:14:15.730
She came in and said, 'Brandon, the dog is gone.

00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:16.460
Something got it.

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:31.747
' I thought because we lived in the country, raccoons or a stray cat had taken the puppy to eat because it was cold.

00:14:31.747 --> 00:14:33.804
Then she heard a squeaking noise.

00:14:33.804 --> 00:14:38.566
Diana went down and looked, and that dog was alive.

00:14:38.566 --> 00:14:44.520
It was frozen cold, but all the guts and blood were gone.

00:14:44.520 --> 00:14:48.680
It was completely restored—no guts, no blood, nothing.

00:15:00.382 --> 00:15:00.618
That dog had been completely mushed; I had crushed the bones, but it was completely restored by the power of God.

00:15:00.618 --> 00:15:05.013
Diana brought the dog in, started blow-drying it, and got it warm.

00:15:05.013 --> 00:15:16.320
Paisley sat there with the biggest grin on her face and said, 'Daddy, I told you all things are possible to him who believes.

00:15:16.320 --> 00:15:22.045
' To this day, I'll never forget her little face, nor your face, nor Braden's face.

00:15:22.045 --> 00:15:28.585
We were all in awe of the goodness of God and the shock of what had happened.

00:15:30.910 --> 00:15:36.103
I held that dog in my hand, and God spoke to me.

00:15:36.103 --> 00:15:43.549
He said, 'Even on your best day, son, your righteousness is filthy rags.

00:15:43.851 --> 00:15:49.685
In the natural, without my Son's blood, you're never good enough.

00:15:49.685 --> 00:15:54.010
' God brought that back to me today regarding the mantle we walk in.

00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:08.183
No matter how you live your life, it's about keeping a relationship with Him and keeping the main thing the main thing, but not touching the trigger.

00:16:08.183 --> 00:16:10.034
What's God's trigger?

00:16:10.034 --> 00:16:11.782
Touching the glory.

00:16:12.605 --> 00:16:19.467
Apart from Him, Jesus said, 'I only do what my Father tells me to do.

00:16:19.467 --> 00:16:27.417
' He did not separate Himself from His Father's voice but always deflected and gave God the praise.

00:16:27.417 --> 00:16:32.983
If the Son of God always gave God the praise, we must do the same.

00:16:34.839 --> 00:16:40.265
In everything you do in word and deed, give all to the glory of God.

00:16:40.265 --> 00:16:59.825
The Bible says that in all we do and say, in word and deed, give all to the glory of God.

00:16:59.825 --> 00:17:08.322
No matter what you're going through, we give all to the glory of God; we stay on God's side.

00:17:08.322 --> 00:17:24.666
As I walked through that, the Lord reminded me—because it was around the same time of year, January—to look back at the Rolodex of miracles seen in life.

00:17:41.620 --> 00:17:42.050
You realize that even then, your righteousness is filthy rags.

00:17:56.413 --> 00:17:56.760
The point the Lord was trying to tell me was, 'Brandon, when you give me praise, it opens the door for the blessing.

00:17:56.760 --> 00:18:11.150
' When you acknowledge Him and tell people, no matter the size of your platform, that you can't do anything apart from Him, it matters.

00:18:11.150 --> 00:18:21.040
Seeing things coming in the future is a gift from Him to show us what is coming.

00:18:21.040 --> 00:18:29.183
Joel chapter 2 says that young men will see visions and old men will dream dreams.

00:18:29.183 --> 00:18:39.189
People ridicule this, but God said, 'Brandon, I'm just fulfilling what I told you I'd do in my Word.

00:18:39.189 --> 00:18:45.451
Someone has to fit the role; why not you?

00:18:45.451 --> 00:18:54.211
' My young men will have visions, my old men will dream dreams, and I'll pour out my Spirit upon my handmaidens.

00:18:54.211 --> 00:19:04.360
Whether it's Acts chapter 2 or Joel chapter 2, God is fulfilling what He said He would do in the last days.

00:19:04.360 --> 00:19:07.960
How many visions qualify?

00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:15.171
'Visions' is plural; it doesn't mean singular.

00:19:15.171 --> 00:19:17.480
He's saying multiple.

00:19:17.480 --> 00:19:20.360
Old men will have multiple dreams.

00:19:20.360 --> 00:19:33.150
If you push into Him and give Him glory, He will show you much more to come, and it will prove accurate.

00:19:33.150 --> 00:19:40.316
It will be a sign for the world to know He is coming.

00:19:42.017 --> 00:19:52.344
The main mission for this channel is to tell His people He is coming and that it's time to repent and get serious about the Father coming.

00:19:58.480 --> 00:19:58.647
I said I'd do it.

00:19:58.647 --> 00:20:07.000
We set out to raise a prayer channel with a million prayer warriors on YouTube.

00:20:07.000 --> 00:20:10.627
By doing so, you will change the course of things.

00:20:10.627 --> 00:20:17.191
Stand strong, keep in His Word, and always deflect the glory.

00:20:17.191 --> 00:20:19.589
It's not about Brandon or Diana.

00:20:23.440 --> 00:20:24.200
I will not take His glory.

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:36.474
Last night in the spirit, we saw Trump negotiating major deals with the Greenland people.

00:20:36.474 --> 00:20:40.020
Europe and the EU were standing strong against Trump, saying they wouldn't allow it.

00:20:44.820 --> 00:20:45.400
I saw them divided in half.

00:20:45.400 --> 00:20:55.933
The elders in Greenland did not want to join the United States, but the young people did.

00:20:55.933 --> 00:21:01.140
They were going to take a major vote to become part of the United States.

00:21:14.149 --> 00:21:14.366
The Trump administration was after minerals.

00:21:22.200 --> 00:21:23.533
I saw billions of dollars of minerals to build batteries and things like that.

00:21:37.823 --> 00:21:38.154
What else was in the dirt?

00:21:38.154 --> 00:21:46.013
I saw big dump trucks circling around; they were going down and getting the minerals.

00:21:46.013 --> 00:21:48.823
I saw fish, which I thought related to cobalt.

00:21:48.823 --> 00:21:50.400
You're still going, right?

00:21:50.400 --> 00:21:52.194
No, I want you to tell me.

00:21:52.194 --> 00:21:55.380
We'll bring our American stores to your shores.

00:21:55.380 --> 00:22:03.508
I saw American stores and big companies going to Greenland to make it like America, like we would do anywhere else.

00:22:03.508 --> 00:22:09.240
You're part of us now, so we'll share what we have.

00:22:09.240 --> 00:22:17.720
An IHOP is going to come there, or a Denny's where you can eat breakfast at night.

00:22:17.720 --> 00:22:20.760
McDonald's is probably already there.

00:22:20.760 --> 00:22:23.040
Starbucks is just around the corner on every block.

00:22:32.760 --> 00:22:32.910
I cracked myself up; it's not even funny, but it's funny to me.

00:22:32.910 --> 00:22:35.840
Dunkin' Donuts is going right next door.

00:22:47.027 --> 00:22:47.284
I saw all these major things coming.

00:22:47.284 --> 00:22:49.520
This is what we saw last night.

00:22:49.520 --> 00:22:56.770
Less than 24 hours, folks, and it happens in the news.

00:22:56.770 --> 00:23:19.657
A lot of times, when we would see things in the past before we started getting on the channel, some things would take two to three months or two to three years.

00:23:19.657 --> 00:23:24.935
He warned us about COVID before we were even on YouTube.

00:23:24.935 --> 00:23:33.112
He told us that summer that a major shaking was coming, and it started happening by March of 2019, I think.

00:23:33.112 --> 00:23:35.891
He spoke to us in 2018.

00:23:35.891 --> 00:23:44.646
He told us COVID was coming, and then he told us another virus is coming after that.

00:23:44.646 --> 00:23:55.893
Read that one right there: 'Trump admin reportedly considers paying each Greenland resident up to 100k amid US takeover talks'—that came out today.

00:23:55.893 --> 00:24:02.800
How much did I tell you they would offer them?

00:24:04.429 --> 00:24:17.453
I saw that the real agreement, whenever it really came down to it, was over $25,000 per citizen to buy their country with our US tax dollars.

00:24:22.895 --> 00:24:28.550
I saw these major things taking place last night in prayer, and it's in the news today, less than 12 hours later.

00:24:28.550 --> 00:24:34.570
People ask, 'Do you work at the news agency, Brandon?

00:24:34.570 --> 00:24:38.497
How did you know that?

00:24:38.497 --> 00:24:41.925
Do you work for the CIA?

00:24:41.925 --> 00:24:44.775
' I've heard that so much lately.

00:24:44.775 --> 00:24:46.185
'You must be Mossad.

00:24:46.185 --> 00:24:47.611
You work for Mossad.

00:24:47.611 --> 00:24:50.320
CIA, you're an operative.

00:24:56.817 --> 00:24:57.131
I know you are.

00:24:57.131 --> 00:25:05.679
You're part of the Masonics, part of that 666 stuff with the witchcraft.

00:25:05.679 --> 00:25:08.040
' Come on, folks.

00:25:08.040 --> 00:25:14.480
I'm a Holy Ghost believer, baptized in the Holy Ghost, praying in the Holy Ghost.

00:25:14.480 --> 00:25:15.560
I'm not CIA.

00:25:32.890 --> 00:25:33.125
I don't work for Mossad.

00:25:33.125 --> 00:25:34.466
It's Jesus.

00:25:34.466 --> 00:25:36.679
Isn't he wonderful?

00:25:49.474 --> 00:25:49.669
That's all I can say to your ignorance.

00:25:49.669 --> 00:25:55.606
Read this one right here: 'US considering investing in critical minerals mining in Greenland, Ammaroq CEO tells CNBC.

00:25:55.606 --> 00:25:57.320
